         <abstract>
            <p>
               This record identifies a collection of texts for the feast of the archangel Raphael, to be read on the 3rd of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Ṗāgʷǝmen</foreign>.
               It consists of a <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7214HomilyJCRuf">homily by John Chrysostom</ref>, two collections of miracles 
               (the unity of the two collections is still to be investigated), two additional texts
               (respectively entitled <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7215HistoryRuf">History of the consecration of the church of Raphael on an island near Alexandria</ref> 
               and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7216HistoryJCRuf">History of how John Chrysostom visited the church of Raphael on an island</ref>) and a 
               <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign>-hymn entitled <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6633SalRufMastafessehe">Salutation to Raphael, who is called 'the Rejoicer'</ref>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
